Auditor-General Tsakani Maluleke is deploying a team of experts to oversee the use of funds related to government’s flood relief efforts and they won't be waiting until the process of disbursing the funds is complete. The team will be monitoring the funds as they are distributed by accounting officers. eNCA Business Editor Devan Murugan spoke to the Auditor-General about her real-time audits. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Auditor-General Tsakani Maluleke is deploying a team of experts to oversee the use of funds related to government’s flood relief efforts. They won't be waiting until the process of disbursing the funds is complete. READ: KZN flood victims allege theft by officials It will be monitoring the funds as they are distributed by accounting officers. Earlier this week, President Cyril  Ramaphosa announced several measures to monitor emergency flood relief funds. He said it was a great shame that the public is debating the potential looting of money following the devastation.